'''Balkh University''' is located in [[Mazari Sharif]], capital of [[Balkh province]], in northern [[Afghanistan]]. Established in 1986, the university currently has about 4000 students and is the second largest in Afghanistan after [[Kabul University]]. 
Faculties include medicine, engineering, economics, journalism, literature, law and science.<ref>[http://iwpr.net/?p=arr&s=f&o=153491&apc_state=heniarr2002 Harsh Lessons at Balkh University]</ref><ref>[http://www.unhcr.org/cgi-bin/texis/vtx/home/opendoc.pdf?tbl=SUBSITES&id=4110b0384 UNHCR - RETURN Information Update]</ref>

The United States and Germany, which leads ISAF in Balkh, have recently announced in Jan 2009 an expansion of Balkh University at a cost of more than 300 million dollars. 

